==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Protocatechuic
<hw>Pro`to*cat`e*chu"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, derived from, or designating, an
organic acid which is obtained as a white crystalline substance from
catechin, asafetida, oil of cloves, etc., and by distillation itself
yields pyrocatechin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Protocercal</ent>⟦br⟧
